Opened the season on fire with a great spring break trip in Clermont, FL in which she batted .400 (12-30) while also driving in eight runs to complement six runs scored which resulted in her being named the Little East Conference Rookie of the Week for her play during the week of March 15-21 ... On March 18 vs. Franciscan University, recorded her most productive game of the year going 4-4 at the plate with three RBI and two runs scored in the Beacons 16-1 victory ... Ended the campaign with 26 RBI to place fourth on the squad and tied for 15th in the Little East Conference ... Drew nine walks on the year and was a perfect 2-2 in stolen base attempts ... From April 7-20, registered an eight-game hitting streak in which she batted a blistering .611 (11-18) while also scoring eight runs to go along with six RBI over that stretch ... Produced 10 multi-hit outings on the season. }
